content.description:
The cracked corner to the right of The Return of Geoff Beene.

Squeeze up the chimney to get to the corner crack. It starts as wide hands and gets wider. Blue camalot to #6 cams were all very helpful but there are a few tricky hand size placements in a horizontal 10ft from the top.

Not a classic but good fun. I used it as a warm up for the fingery classic to the left.
content.protection: Wide hands to wide wide. Though hand size stuff can work in the horizontal up high.
content.location: Just right of The Return of Geoff Beene.

content.description: Locate the obvious  fingercrack that splits the face. Starts with slightly rattly finger jams (depends on hand size). Then goes to perfect finger locks until the anchor. Footholds seem to  appear on the face whenever you start feeling the pump. Excellent climb!!
content.protection: Lot's of finger size cams useful. The crack widens in a couple spots allowing for a #1 camalot to be placed. Two bolt anchor at top of climb.
content.location: Route is located left of where the approach trail hits the wall. Hard to miss it if you walk by.
